My meme

# First meme
inpo1 <- image_read("https://media1.popsugar-assets.com/files/thumbor/-d4lbfPgifoamHBDu_ZV3h9A-AM=/fit-in/1584x1056/top/filters:format_auto():upscale()/2019/08/05/889/n/1922283/tmp_ygenWH_223803119ea27c8e_00496b651a0490188e454f739fd42ed58826b44d7e24b643f520148270385f76de4a51129224a79ce1e29a6ef887c2c2.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(750)

# Second meme
inpo2 <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/10/06/58/10065832a15fbe201a826503300772b2.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# First picture with text
text1 <- image_blank(width = 500,
                     height = 500,
                     color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "me 'IN' the class",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# Second picture with text
text2 <- image_blank(width = 500,
                     height = 500,
                     color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "me 'OFF' the class",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# Combine meme and picture with text
combine_meme <- c(text1,inpo1,text2,inpo2)

# Turning into png
png_meme <- image_append(combine_meme)
image_write(png_meme, "my_meme.png")
# Turning into gif
gif_meme <- image_animate(combine_meme, fps = 1)

image_write(gif_meme, "my_animation.gif")

For creativity,I used more CSS than what was required to change the appearance of my HTML,such like change the body image and the fonts of both header and body. Also,I added a animated GIF in my GitHub repo.

Learning reflection

One of the most important idea I learned from Moudle 1 is to actually create something as a result,since I used to only know how to caculate statistic stuff such like p-value or mean in RStudio,and I thought that is the only way I can use it,so it is really new and interesting for me to learn making our own meme or animated GIF and turn it into a html. Another idea which is important for me is that I realize that materials from class is not the only way I can learn. For example,I wanted to change more visual appearance of my html,so I searched many different ways and learned something more online.

The things related to data technologies that I am really curious about is what else we can bring about by using RStudio and coding.
